EXP NO: 8

AIM :
To write a C++ program to implement a Hospital Patient Record System and to demonstrate member functions defined inside and outside the class.

ALGORITHM :
Start the program.
Define a class named Patient.
Declare data members such as:
patientName
age
disease
roomNumber
Define one member function inside the class (e.g., getDetails()) to take input.
Declare another member function outside the class (displayDetails()) using the scope resolution operator ::.
In the main() function:
Create an object of the Patient class.
Call getDetails() to input data.
Call displayDetails() to display the patient record.
Stop the program.

PROGRAM :
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <limits>
using namespace std;

class Patient {
private:
    string patientName;
    int age;
    string disease;
    int roomNumber;

public:
    // Member function defined INSIDE the class
    void getDetails() {
        cout << "Enter Patient Name: ";
        getline(cin, patientName);
        cout << "Enter Age: ";
        cin >> age;
        cin.ignore(numeric_limits<streamsize>::max(), '\n'); // clear buffer
        cout << "Enter Disease: ";
        getline(cin, disease);
        cout << "Enter Room Number: ";
        cin >> roomNumber;
    }

    // Declaration of member function (to be defined OUTSIDE the class)
    void displayDetails();
};

// Member function defined OUTSIDE the class
void Patient::displayDetails() {
    cout << "\n--- Patient Record ---" << endl;
    cout << "Patient Name : " << patientName << endl;
    cout << "Age          : " << age << endl;
    cout << "Disease      : " << disease << endl;
    cout << "Room Number  : " << roomNumber << endl;
}

int main() {
    Patient p;

    cout << "=== Hospital Patient Record System ===\n";
    cin.ignore(numeric_limits<streamsize>::max(), '\n'); // ensure clean input
    p.getDetails();
    p.displayDetails();

    return 0;

OUTPUT:
Enter Patient Name: John Doe
Enter Age: 45
Enter Disease: Pneumonia
Enter Room Number: 203


Patient Name : John Doe
Age          : 45
Disease      : Pneumonia
Room Number  : 203

 RESULT:
The program successfully demonstrates:
A C++ class with both inside and outside member function definitions.
Use of the scope resolution operator (::).
A Hospital Patient Record System that stores and displays patient details.
